HEADWORD: Siciliano
<hw>Si*ci`li*a"no</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.,
Sicilian.]</ety> <def>A Sicilian dance, resembling the pastorale, set to
a rather slow and graceful melody in 12-8 or 6-8 measure; also, the
music to the dance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

